HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1387
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Robert Brewer upon
being named the 2026 Wildlife Professional of
the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy individual is Robert Brewer, who was recently selected
as the 2026 Wildlife Professional of the Year by the Tennessee Chapter of The Wildlife Society;
and
WHEREAS, the honor of Wildlife Professional of the Year is given annually by the
organization to a deserving professional for outstanding contributions within the State of
Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, a certified wildlife biologist, Mr. Brewer is Professor of Forestry, Wildlife, and
Fisheries and Director of the Greg A. Vital Center for Natural Resources and Conservation at
Cleveland State Community College (CSCC); and
WHEREAS, Robert Brewer came on board with CSCC in 2003, developing courses in
wildlife biology and spearheading the first two-year program for Forestry, Wildlife, and Fisheries
(FWF) in the State; the program was named the 2019 Oustanding Instructional Program by
Community Colleges of Appalachia; and
WHEREAS, he teaches a variety of specialized classes while also ensuring that his
students gain valuable hands-on experience and opportunities to network with professionals in
the field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Brewer has often been duly honored for his good work; in 2023, he was
named the national Student Chapter Advisor of the Year by The Wildlife Society and the
HJR1387
017742
- 1 -

Conservation Educator of the Year by the Tennessee Wildlife Federation; he also received the
Distinguished Faculty Award at CSCC in 2019; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of the University of Tennessee, Knoxville, Robert Brewer holds a
Bachelor of Science degree in Wildlife and Fisheries Science and a Master of Science degree in
Ecology and Evolutionary Biology; he also earned a certificate in surveying technology from
Pellissippi State Community College; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Brewer's continued dedication to his discipline and his students is an
inspiration to all who have the good fortune of knowing him; and
WHEREAS, Robert Brewer epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are characteristic
of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Mr. Brewer for his
dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Robert Brewer upon being named the 2026
Wildlife Professional of the Year by the Tennessee Chapter of The Wildlife Society and extend
to him our best wishes for success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
